
##################################################
inforevealer
by Francois Boulogne <fboulogne at april dot org>
released under the GNU GPL v2 licence
##################################################

The last version of this software could be found at
http://github.com/sciunto/inforevealer


##################################################
Description
##################################################

The goal of this software is to provide easily a 
check-up of useful commands, logfiles or 
configuration files through categories. This 
check-up might be used by people who experiences 
some troubles with their distributions on forums, 
IRC, jabber... Thus, contributors could identify 
quickly problems thanks to relevant information. 


##################################################
Dependances
##################################################

* make
* pygtk 2.6 or greater
* python-configobj 4.6.0 or greater
* python-pexpect

##################################################
Install
##################################################

run:
		make install

By default, the software is installed in /usr.
To modify the path, edit the Makefile at the 
install section:
		"python setup.py install --dir=/usr"
by
		"python setup.py install --dir=/foo/bar"


##################################################
Uninstall
##################################################

run:
		make uninstall

By default, the makefile looks at /usr. Modify the
uninstall section as the install section.

